## Detection

```bash
# Monitor for tag overwrites via CloudTrail
aws cloudtrail lookup-events \
    --lookup-attributes AttributeKey=EventName,AttributeValue=PutImage \
    --query 'Events[].{Time:EventTime,User:Username,Repo:CloudTrailEvent}' \
    --output table

# Detect digest drift — compare running digest against known-good
EXPECTED="sha256:aabbccdd11223344..."
CURRENT=$(crane digest \
    123456789012.dkr.ecr.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/webapp:v1.0.0)

if [ "$CURRENT" != "$EXPECTED" ]; then
    echo "ALERT: Tag v1.0.0 digest changed — possible tampering"
    echo "Expected: $EXPECTED"
    echo "Current:  $CURRENT"
fi
```

