## Fix

```hcl
# ecr-fixed.tf — immutable tags
resource "aws_ecr_repository" "webapp" {
  name                 = "webapp"
  image_tag_mutability = "IMMUTABLE"
}
```

With `IMMUTABLE`, a second push to the same tag fails:

```bash
# Simulated output after enabling immutable tags
docker push 123456789012.dkr.ecr.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/webapp:v1.0.0
# Error: tag v1.0.0 is immutable, cannot be overwritten
```

### Jenkins Pipeline — Reference Images by Digest

```groovy
stage('Deploy') {
    steps {
        script {
            // Always deploy by digest — not tag
            // Digest is captured after push in the Build stage
            sh """
                # Update ECS task definition with digest reference
                aws ecs register-task-definition \
                    --family webapp \
                    --container-definitions '[{
                        "name": "webapp",
                        "image": "${IMAGE_NAME}@${IMAGE_DIGEST}",
                        "portMappings": [{"containerPort": 8080}]
                    }]'
            """
        }
    }
}
```

### Enforce Digest References in ECS Task Definitions

```bash
# Audit running tasks for tag-based image references
aws ecs list-tasks --cluster production | \
    xargs -I{} aws ecs describe-tasks --cluster production --tasks {} \
    --query 'tasks[].containers[].image' --output text | \
    grep -v '@sha256:' | \
    while read img; do
        echo "TAG REFERENCE (not digest): $img"
    done
```
